    "content": "President Hassan Sheikh Mohamud of the Federal Republic of Somalia on Thursday reviewed a military parade and addressed graduates at the TURKSOM training school in Mogadishu. The ceremony marked the completion of a one-year training program for officers and non-commissioned officers, who demonstrated their skills during a joint parade with units under their command.\n\nThe graduates are expected to take up leadership roles in the Somali National Army, reinforcing efforts to rebuild the country's armed forces. The TURKSOM academy, established with Turkish support, has become a cornerstone of Somalia's security sector reform, providing both basic and advanced military instruction.\n\nThis graduation comes at a time when the Somali government is intensifying operations against al-Shabaab and working to take over security responsibilities from the African Union Transition Mission in Somalia (ATMIS). The training focuses on enhancing command capabilities and operational readiness.\n\nFor the Somali diaspora, the development underscores the continued international partnership in stabilizing the country. Many diaspora members have contributed to security sector initiatives, either through remittances or by participating in reconstruction efforts. The professionalization of the armed forces is seen as key to creating a safer environment for investment and return.\n\nRead the original report from Radio Dalsan here: https://radiodalsan.com/2026/07/10/madaxweyne-xasan-oo-tababar-u-soo-xiray-saraakiil/?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=madaxweyne-xasan-oo-tababar-u-soo-xiray-saraakiil",
