    "content": "Somali President Hassan Sheikh Mohamud on Monday officially launched a training course for military officers in Mogadishu. The ceremony took place at a military academy in the capital, attended by senior defense officials.\n\nThe training program is designed to enhance the skills and professionalism of mid-level officers, focusing on modern combat tactics, leadership, and strategic planning. This comes as Somalia continues to rebuild its armed forces after decades of conflict.\n\nPresident Mohamud emphasized the importance of a well-trained military for national stability and the fight against extremist groups. He called on the officers to show dedication and serve the nation with integrity.\n\nThe initiative is part of the federal government's broader security sector reform plan, which aims to gradually transfer security responsibilities from African Union forces to Somali troops. This is a key priority for the current administration.\n\nFor the Somali diaspora, a stable Somalia means greater opportunities for investment and return. Improvements in security also reduce the risk of displacement and enable diaspora support for development projects.\n\nThe training course will run for several weeks, with participants expected to later deploy to various regions. The government has pledged to continue supporting such programs.\n\nRead the original report from Horseed Media here: https://horseedmedia.net/madaxweyne-xasan-sheekh-oo-tababar-u-soo-xiray-saraakiil-ciidan/423603/",
